  <h1>Peretz Partensky</h1>
  <p>Computational biologist. Immigrant. Builder of living systems.</p>
  <p>I grew up between Russia, Israel, and America. I got a PhD in biophysics at UCSF, published in Nature, then spent a decade building startups (Sourcery, YC W13; ImmuneBridge, NK cell immunotherapy). Along the way I coached basketball in Afghanistan, sailed 1,000 miles down the East Coast, got arrested as a Good Samaritan in San Francisco, and recorded 921 hours of voice memos that I'm now indexing with AI.</p>
  <p>I write about immigration, immunology, parenting, and what happens when you point artificial intelligence at your own life.</p>

